# QuipFlip Frontend Environment Variables

# Backend REST API URL
# Development: http://localhost:8000 (direct to local backend)
# Production: /api (proxied through Vercel to Heroku)
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8000

# Note on WebSocket:
# - Development: WebSocket connects directly to local backend (constructs from VITE_API_URL)
# - Production: WebSocket uses token exchange pattern (REST via /api, WebSocket direct to Heroku)
#   No separate environment variable needed - WebSocket URL is hardcoded per environment
